<subSubSection id="C8C9DE727C0541F98957EA25ED013DEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C97407F9E8AF364F4C4B9C0790BF785B" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="984FF8FCB41790F613A478DC35EEEBCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
<bibRefCitation id="8E2EBD2AA0BA2061818459C0000D301F" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to mention this species from Malta, recording both the nominate subspecies and 
<taxonomicName id="BBFD6F9C7DABA714A71134544722E06D" genus="E." lsidName="E. c. subsp. lunulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" rank="subSpecies" species="c." subSpecies="lunulatus">
<emphasis id="70974584A69A2893F924E225E3DD778B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">E. c. lunulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the latter is actually regarded as a junior synonym of the nominate subspecies, which is widely distributed across Europe and reaches China in the East (
<bibRefCitation id="2BE12ECB13BAE67C67CD4512524E23D4" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B13" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1999. Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 11. Die Gattungen Discoelius LATREILLE 1809, Eumenes LATREILLE 1802, Katamenes MEADE-WALDO 1910, Delta SAUSSURE 1855, Ischnogasteroides MAGRETTI 1884 und Pareumenes SAUSSURE 1855. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 31/2: 561-584." title="Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 11. Die Gattungen Discoelius LATREILLE 1809, Eumenes LATREILLE 1802, Katamenes MEADE-WALDO 1910, Delta SAUSSURE 1855, Ischnogasteroides MAGRETTI 1884 und Pareumenes SAUSSURE 1855. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 31 / 2: 561 - 584." year="1999">Gusenleitner 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Females are known to collect the larvae of various 
<taxonomicName id="002C0270072571867F88C182ADF46521" baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1815" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geometridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F5ECEDF8DBFE23C905B15E9671365DA9" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tortricidae</taxonomicName>
as larval provisions.
</paragraph>
